{"title_page": "Fantasy Springs Resort Casino", "text_new": "{{Infobox Casino\n| casino        = Fantasy Springs Resort Casino\n| logo          = Fantasy Springs Resort and Casino logo.gif\n| logo_size     = 250px\n| image         =\n| image_size    = 250px\n| image_caption =\n| location      =\n| coordinates   =\n| address       = 84245 Indio Springs Drive<br>Indio, CA 92203 USA\n| date_opened   = December 21, 2004<ref name = fsr1>{{cite web |author= |title=Fantasy Springs Resort Casino |url=http://www.casenet.com/concert/casinoinfo.htm#fantasysprings |work= |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2010-01-18}}</ref>\n| names_pre     =\n| date_closed   =\n| casino_type   = Indian Casino\n| theme         =\n| owner         = Cabazon Band of Mission Indians\n| architect     =CallisonRTKL Inc.\n| rooms         = 250 <ref> [http://www.fantasyspringsresort.com/prod/resort/resort.php Fantasy Springs Hotel Information]</ref>\n| space_gaming  =\n| shows         =\n| attractions   = ''Special Events Center''<br>''Rock Yard Music''<br>''Fantasy Lanes''<br>''Eagle Falls Golf Course''<br>''Improv Comedy Club<br>Nautilus Fitness Center''\n| renovations   = 2004\n| website       = http://www.fantasyspringsresort.com/\n|Number of Floors=12}}\n\n'''Fantasy Springs Resort Casino''' is a [[casino]] and [[hotel]] located southeast of [[Palm Springs, California]] near [[Interstate 10 in California|I-10]] in [[Indio, California]]. It is owned and operated by the [[Cabazon Band of Mission Indians]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rtkl.com/markets/34/Hospitality.aspx |title=Hospitality |author= |date= |work= |publisher=RTLK Associates |accessdate=2010-02-10}}</ref> a federally recognized tribe. The hotel has 250 rooms and the casino consists of 2000 [[slot machines]] and [[video poker]], 40 tables, and {{convert|100000|sqft|abbr=on}} of special events center space.\n\n==History==\nThe Indio Bingo Palace opened in 1991. In 1995, the Indio Bingo Palace closed and became the Fantasy Springs Casino. In October 2000, the casino underwent an expansion of its casino space.\n\nIn July 2003, Fantasy Springs Casino broke ground on a $145 million resort and a 97,000 square foot conference center. \n\nThe Fantasy Springs Hotel and Casino opened on December 21, 2004 by $200 million refurbishment.<ref name = fsr1/> The property was designed by [[CallisonRTKL|CallisonRTKL Inc.]] (''Previously RTKL Associates Inc.'')<ref name = fsr1/>\n\nIn late April 2007, the 18-hole Eagle Falls Golf Course at Fantasy Springs opened to the public.\n\n==Dining==\n* The Bistro\n* JOY Asian Cuisine\n* POM\n* The Fresh Grill Buffet\n* The Pizza Kitchen\n* Starbucks Coffee\n* Lique\n* LIT\n* 12th Floor Cocktail Lounge & Wine Bar\n* Rocky Mountain Chocolate Factory\n\n==Amenities==\n* Swimming Pool\n* Special Events Center\n* Rock Yard Music <small>(Fridays and Saturdays)</small>\n* Fantasy Lanes\n* Eagle Falls Golf Course\n* Improv Comedy Club\n* Nautilus Fitness Center\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.fantasyspringsresort.com/ Official Website]\n* [http://www.eaglefallsgolfcourse.com/ Eagle Falls Golf Course.com]{{Dead link|date=December 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n{{coord|33.721|-116.194|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Cahuilla]]\n[[Category:Casinos in Riverside County, California]]\n[[Category:Casino hotels]]\n[[Category:Indio, California]]\n[[Category:Native American casinos]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Casino\n| casino        = Fantasy Springs Resort Casino\n| logo          = Fantasy Springs Resort and Casino logo.gif\n| logo_size     = 250px\n| image         =\n| image_size    = 250px\n| image_caption =\n| location      =\n| coordinates   =\n| address       = 84245 Indio Springs Drive<br>Indio, CA 92203 USA\n| date_opened   = December 21, 2004<ref name = fsr1>{{cite web |author= |title=Fantasy Springs Resort Casino |url=http://www.casenet.com/concert/casinoinfo.htm#fantasysprings |work= |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2010-01-18}}</